===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|quaken|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|cwacian||to quake, tremble, chatter|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*kwakōną||to shake, quiver, tremble}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*gʷog-||to shake, swing}}, related to {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|cweccan||to shake, swing, move, vibrate, shake off, give up|lang=ang}} (see {{l|en|quitch}}), <!--{{etyl|frs|-}} {{term|kwakkelje||to flounder, limp|lang=frs}},--> {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|kwakkelen||to ail, be ailing|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Quackelei||chattering|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|kvakle||to bungle|lang=da}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|vēxō||toss, shake violently, jostle, vex|lang=la}}, {{etyl|ga|-}} {{term|bogadh||a move, movement, shift, change|lang=ga}}.

